org.apache.sis.index

Class GeoHashCoder

  • Object
    • GeoHashCoder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GeoHashCoder
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Encodes geographic coordinates as geohashes strings, and decode such strings back to coordinates. The current implementation is restricted to two-dimensional geographic coordinates, in the (longitude, latitude) order with the longitudes ranging from -180° to 180° and the latitudes ranging from -90° to 90°. The datum is unspecified.
    Since:
    0.1
    See Also:
    Wikipedia: Geohash, Serialized Form

    Defined in the sis-storage module

        Parameters:

      • encode

        public String encode(DirectPosition position)
        Encodes the given position into a geohash. The current implementation takes the first ordinate value as the longitude, the second ordinate value as the latitude, then delegates to encode(double, double).

        The current implementation does not verify the Coordinate Reference System of the given position. However this may change in future SIS versions.

        Parameters:
        position - The coordinate to encode.
        Returns:
        Geohash encoding of the given position.

      • decode

                      throws ParseException
        Decodes the given geohash into a longitude and a latitude.
        Parameters:
        geohash - Geohash string to decode.
        Returns:
        A new position with the longitude at ordinate 0 and latitude at ordinate 1.
        Throws:
        ParseException - If an error occurred while parsing the given string.
